[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Since transfer learning makes use of training with multiple objective functions it is related to cost-sensitive machine learning and multi-objective optimization.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] In 1976, Bozinovski and Fulgosi published a paper addressing transfer learning in neural network training.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] The paper gives a mathematical and geometrical model of the topic.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] In 1981, a report considered the application of transfer learning to a dataset of images representing letters of computer terminals, experimentally demonstrating positive and negative transfer learning.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] In 1992, Lorien Pratt formulated the discriminability-based transfer (DBT) algorithm.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] By 1998, the field had advanced to include multi-task learning, along with more formal theoretical foundations.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Influential publications on transfer learning include the book *Learning to Learn* in 1998, a 2009 survey and a 2019 survey.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Ng said in his NIPS 2016 tutorial that TL would become the next driver of machine learning commercial success after supervised learning.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] In the 2020 paper, "Rethinking Pre-Training and self-training", Zoph et al. reported that pre-training can hurt accuracy, and advocate self-training instead.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] The definition of transfer learning is given in terms of domains and tasks.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] A domain ${\mathcal {D}}$ consists of: a feature space ${\mathcal {X}}$ and a marginal probability distribution $P(X)$ , where $X=\{x_{1},...,x_{n}\}\in {\mathcal {X}}$ .
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Given a specific domain, ${\mathcal {D}}=\{{\mathcal {X}},P(X)\}$ , a task consists of two components: a label space ${\mathcal {Y}}$ and an objective predictive function $f:{\mathcal {X}}\rightarrow {\mathcal {Y}}$ .
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] The function f is used to predict the corresponding label $f(x)$ of a new instance x .
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Algorithms for transfer learning are available in Markov logic networks and Bayesian networks.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Transfer learning has been applied to cancer subtype discovery, building utilization, general game playing, text classification, digit recognition, medical imaging and spam filtering.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] It was noted that this relationship worked in both directions, showing that EEG brainwaves can likewise be used to classify EMG signals.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] The experiments noted that the accuracy of neural networks and convolutional neural networks were improved through transfer learning both prior to any learning (compared to standard random weight distribution) and at the end of the learning process (asymptote).
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] That is, results are improved by exposure to another domain.
[src:fastai/transfer-learning] Moreover, the end-user of a pre-trained model can change the structure of fully-connected layers to improve performance.
